	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Destiny of an Emperor actually does something similar when entering in battle.</div>
<br />
<br />And this effect totally destroys some emulators.  A couple I've used slow down to a total crawl (music/sound impacted as well).  I've seen the same thing happen with Bionic Commando's title screen.
<br />
<br />I've always been curious how they do it (mid-scanline PPU trickery, or do they convert sprites into tiles then change the CHR data using CPU code)...  actually, fuck it -- I don't want to know how they did it.  I'd rather appreciate the mystery, just like the scaling "IV" in Dragon Quest 4 (not Dragon Warrior 4!).  I must be the only technically-savvy person these days who doesn't want to know how everything works (and I'm an Aquarius! Go figure!)
<br />
<br />Another game which uses a similar fading effect is Shadowgate.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


